{"type":"message","id":"cc478515","parentId":"33215856","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:34:02.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is asking about the MC watchdog file I saw in the memory directory earlier. Let me check what that file contains.","thinkingSignature":"702297d4e8c627d26778c7f324909bf7bb45035774990c20a8d3195ac4c3f087"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1zhdxozrqvl6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace/memory/mc-watchdog-issue.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37110,"output":67,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37305,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777685640146,"responseId":"064487881e491f91280e02185a4a046d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"36ac45b6","parentId":"cc478515","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:34:03.250Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1zhdxozrqvl6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-01 - MC Watchdog Cron Issue\n\n## Problem\nMC watchdog cron (scheduled every 10 min) is failing with:\n```\nexec denied: Cron runs cannot wait for interactive exec approval.\nEffective host exec policy: security=allowlist ask=on-miss askFallback=deny\n```\n\n## Root Cause\nThe cron session runs with `security=allowlist` and `ask=on-miss`, which means any command not in the exec allowlist requires interactive approval. The mc-watch.sh script is not in the allowlist.\n\n## Fix Options\n1. **Approve interactively**: Bobby needs to run `openclaw approvals get --gateway` and approve the command\n2. **Add to allowlist**: Run once interactively to cache the approval, or:\n   ```\n   openclaw approvals allow -- /bin/bash /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/scripts/mc-watch.sh\n   ```\n3. **Change security policy**: Set `tools.exec.security=\"full\"` and `tools.exec.ask=\"off\"` in gateway config\n\n## Note\nThe mc-watch.sh script handles recovery automatically (restarting MC server if down). If the server is actually running, no action needed.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777685643250}}
{"type":"message","id":"a26a294c","parentId":"36ac45b6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:34:12.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It was a watchdog cron for the Mission Control server that was failing due to exec security policy. Bobby's MC (Mission Control) server runs on port 8787. The watchdog script checks if it's running and restarts it if not.\n\nThe issue was back in April 1st - the mc-watch.sh script wasn't allowed to run via cron because the cron sessions use `security=allowlist` which blocks unapproved commands. The fix was either to approve it, add it to allowlist, or Bobby already addressed it.\n\nLet me give him the quick summary.","thinkingSignature":"43c0c86ee4a62871ee026e4d77b7c2a18f2d36734bc70dc6a1323f32c1bbcbf0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**MC Watchdog** was a cron job monitoring your **Mission Control server** (port 8787).\n\n**What it does:** Every 10 minutes it runs `mc-watch.sh` — if MC server is down, it auto-restarts it.\n\n**The issue (Apr 1):** Cron sessions run with a restricted exec policy (`allowlist`), so the watchdog script was being blocked.\n\n**Fixes mentioned:**\n1. Approve interactively via `openclaw approvals get --gateway`\n2. Add to exec allowlist permanently\n3. Switch cron sessions to `security=full`\n\nSince MC server is listed as a **permanent LaunchAgent service** in your TOOLS.md, the watchdog either got fixed or isn't needed anymore since LaunchAgents auto-restart on crash anyway.\n\nWant me to check if it's still configured / working?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":325,"output":286,"cacheRead":37216,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37827,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777685643251,"responseId":"0644878bef8056379e9ca308423f734e"}}
