{"type":"message","id":"1fd4d1ff","parentId":"bd816cff","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:16:56.397Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pz5nlo3e8zop_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/The-OpenClaw-Guide-FULL-PREVIEW.html."}],"details":{"diff":"      ...\n  586     <p class=\"chapter-subtitle\">OpenClaw turned my MacBook into a real workhorse.</p>\n  587   </div>\n  588 \n  589   <h2>The Story Behind OpenClaw</h2>\n- 590   <p>OpenClaw was created by <strong>Peter Steinberger</strong> — an Austrian developer who spent 13 years building <strong>PSPDFKit</strong>, a PDF company that ended up powering document handling on over a <strong>billion devices</strong>. We're talking Apple, Dropbox, all the big players. In 2023, he sold that company for reportedly around <strong>€100 million</strong>. By all accounts, he made it. He was done. Retired.</p>\n+ 590   <p>OpenClaw was created by <strong>Peter Steinberger</strong> — an Austrian developer who spent 13 years building <strong>PSPDFKit</strong>, a PDF company that ended up powering document handling on over a <strong>billion devices</strong>. We're talking Apple, Dropbox, all the big players. In 2023, he sold that company for reportedly around <strong>$110 million</strong>. By all accounts, he made it. He was done. Retired.</p>\n  591   <p>Except... he wasn't really done. He was <em>burned out</em>.</p>\n  592   <p>\"I felt like Austin Powers where they suck the mojo out,\" Peter told Lex Fridman in an interview. \"I couldn't get code out anymore. I was just, like, staring and feeling empty.\"</p>\n  593   <p>So he did what any burnt-out tech millionaire would do — he traveled. Partied. Tried therapy. Nothing stuck. He was looking for meaning and couldn't find it.</p>\n  594   <p>Then in April 2025, something changed. He was tinkering with a Twitter analysis tool and realized AI had shifted. The tools could finally handle the boring parts of coding, leaving him free to just <em>build</em>. So he got back in the game.</p>\n      ...","firstChangedLine":590},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777688216396}}
{"type":"message","id":"60ea6b5b","parentId":"1fd4d1ff","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:17:00.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also need to update the md source file.\n","thinkingSignature":"7ae951e54fbe13814170214d00500045bdd375d86c1230e147564b5a03c83875"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nAlso updating the source markdown file:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fhw65u5vlyjh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"In 2023, he sold that company for reportedly around **$110 million**","oldText":"In 2023, he sold that company for reportedly around **€100 million**"}],"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":249,"output":128,"cacheRead":74624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777688216401,"responseId":"0644919825d9b684ab245929528219f8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"51a73688","parentId":"60ea6b5b","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:17:00.573Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fhw65u5vlyjh_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\\nCurrent file contents:\\n# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\\n\\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Section 1: What is OpenClaw?\\n\\n### What Is OpenClaw?\\n\\nOpenClaw is an **autonomous AI agent** that runs on your computer — think of it like having a digital employee who lives on your MacBook. It's always working, always monitoring, always ready to help. Unlike ChatGPT where you open it, ask a question, close it, and it's gone — OpenClaw stays running in the background. It checks your email, manages your files, runs automations, sends you updates, and handles all the repetitive stuff you'd otherwise have to do yourself.\\n\\nHere's what makes it different from other AI tools:\\n\\n**It's local.** OpenClaw runs on your own machine, not in some distant data center. Your data stays\\n... (truncated)\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Could not find the exact text in /Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-1-What-is-OpenClaw.md. The old text must match exactly including all whitespace and newlines.\nCurrent file contents:\n# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\n\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\n\n---\n\n## Section 1: What is OpenClaw?\n\n### What Is OpenClaw?\n\nOpenClaw is an **autonomous AI agent** that runs on your computer — think of it like having a digital employee who lives on your MacBook. It's always working, always monitoring, always ready to help. Unlike ChatGPT where you open it, ask a question, close it, and it's gone — OpenClaw stays running in the background. It checks your email, manages your files, runs automations, sends you updates, and handles all the repetitive stuff you'd otherwise have to do yourself.\n\nHere's what makes it different from other AI tools:\n\n**It's local.** OpenClaw runs on your own machine, not in some distant data center. Your data stays\n... (truncated)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777688220573}}
