kill template explanation\n- Ends with `[Attached as separate file: Morning-Brief-Skill-Template.md]` then DRAFT notices for sections 8-10\n\n**Section 8** ✅ Complete\n- 6 real-world workflows (YouTube pipeline, content repurposing, multi-agent ops, etc.)\n- References \"Alex Finn\" — sounds like a real case study Bobby is citing\n- Strong closing line: \"Master one, add the next...\"\n\n**Section 9** ✅ Complete\n- 6 advanced techniques (Reverse Prompting, Heartbeat Trick, Memory Flush, etc.)\n- Minor flag: \"Heartbeat Trick\" mentions pricing that could date — minor\n- Great closing: \"That's when OpenClaw stops being a tool and starts being a team member.\"\n\n**Section 10** ✅ (truncated in audit, appears complete)\n- 7 money-making use cases + \"force multiplication\" theme tying it all together\n\n---\n\n**Issues to fix:**\n\n1. **All sections end with `*More sections coming soon...*`** — needs actual closing lines appropriate to each section's topic\n\n2. **Section 10 may have been truncated** — need to verify the full content\n\n3. **The €100M → $110M change** was only made in Section 1 HTML and .md file — other sections that reference Peter/PSPDFKit should be checked too\n\n4. **Section 7 ends with file reference** — clean but needs a final paragraph closing it out properly\n\n**What needs your input vs what I can fix myself:**\n- I can remove all the `*More sections coming soon...*` placeholder text and replace with proper closings\n- I can update any other currency references if Peter appears in other sections\n- The \"Alex Finn\" reference in Section 8 — is that a real person you're citing?\n- Section 10 — confirm it's actually complete\n\nWant me to start cleaning up the placeholder endings and flagging anything that needs YOUR eyes?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71286,"output":815,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72357,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0