{"type":"message","id":"73215c02","parentId":"077855f5","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:41:06.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby's asking about why I send multiple texts in a row. Let me look at this screenshot to understand what he's referring to. He sent the same screenshot earlier but I already addressed that.\n\nActually wait - he's asking about \"multiple texts in a row saying that you are on it\" - this might be referring to earlier in this session when I said something like \"On it\" or \"I'm on it\" multiple times. Let me look back at the conversation.\n\nLooking at the conversation - when he said \"you know what i honestly do not want to do this right know lmao\" I responded with \"Haha no worries Bobby. It's there whenever you want to come back to it. Not going anywhere. 🤖\" then he asked \"is there anything you can do for me to make this openclaw guide more complete?\" and I said \"Yeah — here's what I can do right now while you rest:\" and listed things. Then he said \"i want you to also audit section 1 as well dont forget that one too. i know there are some sections we havent completed as well.\" and I said \"On it. Spinning up a sub-agent to read through all 10 sections right now — every markdown file, every section.\" and then said \"I'll text you when it's done — should be within a few minutes.\"\n\nI don't think I sent multiple texts saying \"on it\" in a row. The screenshot he sent appears to be the same one from earlier (the cover page). \n\nActually - maybe there were multiple instances where I sent texts like \"Done!\" or \"Updated\" in succession? Or maybe when I was working through the edits I sent multiple confirmations? Or when I was processing the subagent results?\n\nActually I think I see what might be happening. When I was fixing things (the title change, the €100M change, adding the Peter Steinberger story, removing the stats bar) - each time I said something brief like \"Done!\" after each one. Maybe that felt like a lot of separate texts.\n \nI should just acknowledge his feedback directly rather than continuing to explain - he's clearly noticed a pattern and I want to take that seriously.\n","thinkingSignature":"8c9798318a60edd7504641c52d2da5d71dcac8142109e9ee3b3ab6c8029dcc2d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nNo excuse — that was me being inefficient. When I'm working through a list of small edits, I'll just batch them into one message instead of sending \"Done.\" after each one. Won't happen again. 🤖"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83330,"output":483,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83941,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777689626368,"responseId":"0644971b0dfbe0d2bc329068a0e630c4"}}
