{"type":"message","id":"fd6a72cf","parentId":"8b28cbbf","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:26:24.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants a form that he can fill out - questions that I can use to rewrite Sections 8, 9, and 10 in his voice and based on his personal experience with OpenClaw. This is a good idea. Let me create a form with questions that cover:\n\n1. Sections 8 (Real-World Workflows) - content creation, brand building, YouTube\n2. Section 9 (Advanced Techniques) - reverse prompting, multi-agent setups, etc.\n3. Section 10 (Money-Making Use Cases) - this should be very personal since Bobby's goal is to sell the guide\n\nThe form should capture:\n- His specific workflows and automations\n\n\n- What he actually uses OpenClaw for\n- His voice and how he talks about things\n- Personal stories and examples\n- What he wants readers to get out of it\n- His money-making goals\n\nI should create this as an HTML file and open it in Xcode so Bobby can fill it out and send it back. The questions need to be specific enough to get good content but not overwhelming - things like what workflows and automations he actually runs daily, his content creation process, specific examples of times OpenClaw solved a problem for him, and what he considers his biggest wins.\n\nI also need to understand how he'd personally explain OpenClaw's value to someone, what he wants readers to feel after finishing the guide, whether he has a YouTube channel or social media presence, and what his income goals are and how OpenClaw fits into them.\n","thinkingSignature":"9d1850c2c13a19081e8c6a4c414c5b45eec7927ed7c0f10550854c055b5c5bd2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ne1hvhktadd4_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# OpenClaw Guide — Bobby's Voice & Experience Form\n\n*A guide written in YOUR voice, based on YOUR experience. Fill this out and I'll rewrite Sections 8, 9, and 10 to sound exactly like you.*\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 8: Real-World Workflows\n*Content creation, brand building, YouTube, music career*\n\n---\n\n**1. What workflows or automations do you actually run daily?**\nList what OpenClaw does for you on a typical day — from when you wake up to when you sleep.\n\n**2. How do you use OpenClaw for content creation?**\nYouTube, social media, writing — what do you actually use it for? What's your process?\n\n**3. Do you have a YouTube channel or are you planning one? What's it about?**\nIf yes, what content do you make? If no, what content would you want to make?\n\n**4. Tell me about a specific time OpenClaw saved you time or helped you create something.**\nGive me a real example — what happened, what did OpenClaw do, what was the result?\n\n**5. What's the blank-page problem for you?**\nWhen you're stuck on content, what do you do? How does OpenClaw help you get started?\n\n**6. For your music career — how do you use OpenClaw?**\nContent, brand, fan engagement, logistics — what's your actual setup?\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 9: Advanced Techniques\n*Reverse prompting, multi-agent setups, proactive automation*\n\n---\n\n**7. What's a skill or workflow you built that felt like a breakthrough?**\nSomething that made everything click — what was it and why did it work?\n\n**8. How do you actually use reverse prompting?**\nWalk me through a real example of when you used it and how it helped.\n\n**9. Do you run multiple agents? What's your setup?**\nTell me about your agent team — what does each one do and how do they work together?\n\n**10. What's the heartbeat trick mean to you?**\nHow do you use it in your own setup? What does it automate for you?\n\n**11. What part of OpenClaw felt the most \"magic\" when it finally clicked?**\nThe moment you thought — okay, this is actually powerful.\n\n**12. What's something you wish you knew earlier about OpenClaw?**\nThe one thing that would've saved you the most time if you'd known it on day one.\n\n---\n\n## SECTION 10: Money-Making Use Cases\n*How to turn OpenClaw into income*\n\n---\n\n**13. What's your actual goal with this guide?**\nDo you want to sell it? Use it to attract clients? Build a YouTube channel around it? All of the above?\n\n**14. How do you plan to make money with OpenClaw?**\nYou've mentioned YouTube, selling the guide, maybe building tools — what's your actual plan?\n\n**15. What income would make this worth it for you?**\nBallpark — what number would make you feel like this effort paid off?\n\n**16. What's your own experience with making money online?**\nHave you sold things before? YouTube income? Services? Affiliate? Tell me what you know.\n\n**17. If someone bought this guide and did everything in it — what should their result be?**\nWhat should they be able to accomplish? Paint the picture of success.\n\n---\n\n## YOUR VOICE\n\n**18. How do you describe OpenClaw to someone who's never heard of it?**\nWrite it like you're telling a friend at dinner. What do you say?\n\n**19. What's the one thing you want people to feel after reading this guide?**\nExcited? Empowered? Relieved? Clear? Something else?\n\n**20. Is there anything you want to add — stories, examples, things I missed?**\nAnything you want in this guide that I haven't asked about?\n\n---\n\n*Fill this out and send it back to me. I'll use your exact words to rewrite Sections 8, 9, and 10 so they sound like you wrote them, not me.*","path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Bobby-Voice-Form.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92281,"output":1211,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777692350252,"responseId":"0644a1bf319670fbbec0856d5805ce50"}}
