{"type":"message","id":"9a0ab91c","parentId":"adec4fc6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:56:54.307Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The link that works is when I send it as a plain markdown link in the Telegram message. The one that worked earlier was:\n`[https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html](https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html)`\n\nSo when I use the message tool to send it, it's not working. But when I just write it as a regular response, it works.\n\nWait - when I sent it as a regular response (just text in the chat), it worked. But when I sent it via the message tool, it didn't.\n\nActually looking more carefully at what happened earlier:\n\n\n- I sent the message via text response, not the message tool\n- I tried again with the message tool and it didn't work\n- The working format was plain text markdown link sent directly\n\nSo the issue is that the message tool is stripping the clickability. When I send it as a plain text response in this session, it works. But when I use the message tool, it doesn't. That's why in Telegram the message tool works fine but here in webchat it's not working.\n\nWait, actually looking at the context - Bobby is in Telegram. When I send via the message tool (which goes to Telegram), the links are NOT clickable. When I respond as a plain text message in this session, the links ARE clickable (in the webchat interface).\n\nBut Bobby sees these responses in Telegram. So if I respond as text in the session, it goes to Telegram as a text message - and in the earlier test, the markdown link DID work in Telegram. So the issue now is that when I use the message tool, it renders differently in Telegram.\n\nLet me look at what worked earlier in this very conversation. When I wrote `👉 [https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html](https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net/telephone.html)` in my regular response text, it was clickable for Bobby in Telegram. But when I used the message tool with the same format, it wasn't. The working format was plain text in a regular response.\n\nSo the fix is: send links as plain text in my responses, NOT via the message tool.\n\nBut then Bobby earlier said \"you did not just send me a link that i can click on. fix it dean.\" - which means I sent it as text but it wasn't clickable. So something is inconsistent.\n\nLet me just try plain text responses going forward and see if the links are clickable for Bobby in Telegram. The working format appears to be: `👉 [text](url)` as a plain text response in the session.\n","thinkingSignature":"a55926eda290000797e4c54ba7a9674a6ef3e9039d4ca52abaa3e0b26b66d659"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI'm sending it as a direct text reply now — see if this is clickable:\n\n👉 [http://localhost:8765/voice-form.html](http://localhost:8765/voice-form.html)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":103484,"output":613,"cacheRead":352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104449,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777694198714,"responseId":"0644a8f7ad7901af0c3a1a2020cf7df6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d870cb29","parentId":"9a0ab91c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T03:59:11.018Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"this is what cody does when he send his links that i can click on or tap to open the page. this is what he said: Super easy fix Bobby! Here's the secret:\n\n───\n\nHow Links Become Clickable\n\nTelegram auto-detects links when they're formatted correctly:\n\n| Format | Will it click? |\n| ----------------------------------- | -------------- |\n| http://example.com | ✅ Yes |\n| https://example.com | ✅ Yes |\n| [click here](http://example.com) | ✅ Yes |\n| Check it out: http://example.com | ✅ Yes |\n| Check it out: example.com (no http) | ❌ No |\n| http://example.com (in code) | ❌ No |\n| http:// example.com (with space) | ❌ No |───\n\nWhat Dean Should Do\n\nRIGHT:\n\nCheck it out: http://100.103.22.35:8789WRONG:\n\nHere's the link: http://100.103.22.35:8789 ← code block breaks it\nHere's the link: http://100.103.22.35:8789. ← period at end can break it\nhere's the link: (http://100.103.22.35:8789) ← parentheses sometimes break───\n\nQuick Fix for Dean\n\nTell Dean to just send the URL plain, without any formatting around it. Just drop the raw URL in the message:\n\n✅ Open it here: http://your-site.com\n✅ http://your-site.com (URL on its own line)\n\n───\n\nWhy It's Breaking\n\nMost likely Dean is:\n\n1. Putting the URL in a code block (```)\n2. Wrapping it in backticks `\n3. Not including http:// or https://\n4. Adding punctuation right after the URL\n\n───\n\nJust tell Dean: \"Send the URL plain, no code blocks, no backticks, make sure http:// is there\"\n\nThat's it! 🎯"}],"timestamp":1777694350950}}
