{"type":"message","id":"e4db21d8","parentId":"ac2d9461","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:10:34.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is still unable to click on the link. Let me try a different approach - maybe I can use the Tailscale URL since that's the public-facing URL that Bobby uses. Let me check what Tailscale URL I can use.\n\nFrom the earlier status check, Bobby's Tailscale exposure was:\n`bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net · https://bobbys-macbook-air-1.tail358b13.ts.net`\n\nSo I could try hosting this on the Tailscale URL instead of localhost. Let me try using the Tailscale serve to expose the form, or just try the raw Tailscale URL format.\n\n\nActually, the real issue is that localhost links won't work since Bobby's accessing from Telegram on his phone, not from the same MacBook. I need to use the Tailscale URL instead, but I'm not sure if the Python server is set up to handle requests from the Tailscale interface.\n\nLet me think about alternative approaches like ngrok, but the simplest solution is probably just to send Bobby a note asking him to open the form directly from his browser on that machine since the server's already running locally there. I'm realizing the localhost URL won't work for Bobby since he's accessing from Telegram on his phone, not the same MacBook where the server is running. I need to either set up Tailscale to expose the local server or use ngrok to create a public URL that will work across devices. the Tailscale URL. Let me just be honest with Bobby about the situation - the localhost URL only works on his MacBook, so I either need to set up Tailscale (which requires gateway configuration I can't do right now), use ngrok, or help him open the file directly in Safari instead.","thinkingSignature":"e1c7171cd9d6147b84866c264e288b0171b525ee5e33b54d61e18d748b6fc7c5"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n\nYou're right — the issue is `localhost` only works on your MacBook. Since you're on Telegra